CHINA JAILS TV WITNESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Chinese man arrested after being interviewed on ABC television about the 
military assault in Beijing was sentenced to 10 years in prison. The man, Xiao 
Bin, 42, a factory worker from Dalian, was identified and apprehended after 
Chinese television showed the interview. He was accused of "spreading 
counterrevolutionary lies." In Sichuan province in central China, two men were 
executed for offenses during rioting in early June in response to the violence 
in Beijing. Their deaths brought to 29 the number reported executed since the 
crackdown. 
