<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALVADOR REBELS BLAMED IN CAR BOMB EXPLOSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN SALVADOR 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A powerful car bomb exploded outside El Salvador's tallest building -- the 
18-story Democracy Tower -- on Thursday, shattering windows but causing no 
serious injuries, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Although no group claimed responsibility, the government blamed it on leftist 
rebels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
