EUROPE'S POPULATION RISES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BRUSSELS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The population of the 12 European Community countries has risen to more than 
325 million, but almost half the increase in the past year is due to 
immigration, the statistical office Eurostat said Thursday. On Jan. 1, 1989, 
the community's population reached 325,472,000, an increase of 1,277,000 from 
1988 figures, Eurostat said. 
