<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEAR AGAIN SEEN PROWLING IN TAHOE AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STATELINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A large, hungry and curious black bear that has been prowling Lake Tahoe 
neighborhoods for food during the last few days was spotted again Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The bear was sighted at about 1 a.m. near Chimney Rock, midway up Kingsbury 
Grade, which leads to the Stateline casino district along the south shore, 
Douglas County Sheriff's Sgt. Al Baumruck said. 
</P>
<P>
Baumruck said that because of the reported size of the bear, deputies believe 
it is the same one seen previously going through trash cans for food and 
peeking into house windows during the last few days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
