<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: VIETNAM VETS' GROUP STAGES VA PROTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A dozen members of a new group called Vietnam Veterans in Recovery gathered 
outside the Veterans Administration Medical Center in West Los Angeles on 
Thursday to protest cuts in special treatment for people suffering 
post-traumatic stress disorder. 
</P>
<P>
Their complaint centered on a 2-year-old program that is being discontinued at 
the 600-acre West Los Angeles facility. The program has provided one full-time 
psychiatrist and a part-time social worker to aid those with the disease. 
</P>
<P>
Veterans Administration officials said the program is not being discontinued 
altogether but is being moved to a downtown outpatient facility at 4th and Hill 
streets. The protesting veterans argued that facility is highly inconvenient 
for them. 
</P>
