<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: AILING ANTONOVICH TAKEN TO HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County Supervisor Mike Antonovich has been hospitalized at St. 
Joseph Medical Center in Burbank, suffering from pneumonia, his chief deputy 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Silver said he spoke to the supervisor by telephone late Thursday, and, "He 
was very chipper. He is putting in a work day over there." 
</P>
<P>
Antonovich was driven to the hospital early Wednesday, after leaving work 
Monday with a fever. Silver said a nurse took Antonovich's temperature in the 
office Monday morning, "and it was over 104" degrees. 
</P>
<P>
Silver said Antonovich's temperature was "close to normal" Thursday. He said he 
expects the supervisor to remain in the hospital through the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
Antonovich's sprawling 5th District takes in the Antelope and Santa Clarita 
valleys, Burbank, Glendale, Pasadena and a large part of the San Fernando 
Valley. 
</P>
