<P>
COMPTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The report on present-day Compton ("Black Middle Class Keeps the Faith for 
Compton," Part I, June 26) and its proud residents is a lucid testimonial not 
only on pride of ownership, but also pride of community. 
</P>
<P>
The article should be read by all ethnic groups who, despite social stigma and 
stereotypes nurtured by bigots believing in "exclusive neighborhoods," continue 
to think that the latter is the sole way to go on the road to the American 
success story. The Compton story defies this. 
</P>
