<HEADLINE>
<P>
STURGES TO ATTEND MASTER'S FOR BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joe Sturges, a catcher from Thousand Oaks High who played baseball and football 
the past two years at Southern Utah State, signed a letter of intent this week 
to attend The Master's College. 
</P>
<P>
Sturges, who will enter Master's as a junior, batted .315 with 4 home runs and 
33 runs batted in last season at Southern Utah, which dropped its baseball 
program in June. Master's has no football program. 
</P>
