<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 AREA SAILORS IN WORLD YOUTH CHAMPIONSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ryan Cox and K. C. Alfred of Thousand Oaks will set sail Tuesday in Montreal as 
the U. S. Youth Sailing team competes in the International Yacht Racing Union 
World Youth Sailing Championships . 
</P>
<P>
Cox, a 1989 graduate of Westlake High, and Alfred, who will be a senior at 
Westlake this fall, qualified for the team by winning the double-handed 
Collegiate 420 class title in the U. S. Youth Championships, June 30 in 
Hyannisport, Mass. 
</P>
<P>
Cox and Alfred, representing the Ventura Yacht Club, rallied from second place 
in the points standings to win the championship in the final two days of 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
Their performance at the Hyannis Yacht Club also qualified them as members of 
the U. S. Yacht Racing Union/Rolex Junior Sailing Team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Sidebar 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071489-0073 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 82021 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 14, 1989, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
