<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Aleene MacMinn, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bon Jovi, Motley Crue, Scorpions, Cinderella and Skid Row are some of the rock 
acts booked for the Moscow Music Peace Festival Aug. 12-13. Four hours of the 
Aug. 13 rocking in Moscow will be seen in this country on a prime-time, 
pay-per-view TV special that will be simulcast on radio by Westwood One. The 
peace festival is being sponsored by the Make a Difference Foundation, which is 
dedicated to combating drug and alcohol abuse among youth. Funds from the 
festival will be shared by U.S. and Soviet organizations that work with young 
substance abusers. Aleene MacMinn 
</P>
