<TEXT>
<P>
St. Louis, a member of the Major Indoor Soccer League for nine seasons until 
the Steamers folded last year, has been awarded an expansion franchise for the 
1989-90 season. 
</P>
<P>
The team will be owned by Milan Mandaric, a San Jose businessman, and its 
roster is expected to include several players who either grew up in St. Louis 
or played with the Steamers. Former Steamers scheduled to join the team are 
midfielder Darryl Doran, defenders Steve Trittschuh and Mark Frederickson and 
goaltender Slobo Ilijevski. 
</P>
<P>
Doran and Frederickson were selected in the league's dispersal draft of players 
from the Los Angeles Lazers, which ceased operations last month. 
