<P>
Housing Completions Fall: The Commerce Department reported that the number of 
new American homes and apartment buildings completed during May fell by 7.5% to 
the lowest level in six months. The May drop, following a revised 6.4% rise in 
April, was down 1.7% from a year ago. May housing completions stood at a 
seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.436 million, the lowest since November, 
1988, when the rate was 1.429 million. Aside from the steep fall in the 
Northeast, home completions fell 7.4% in the Midwest, 5.3% in the South and 
2.6% in the West. 
