<P>
ARSON SUSPECTED IN FIRE AT AWNING COMPANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Ana fire investigators said Thursday that a $1-million fire last weekend 
that destroyed a Santa Ana awning firm was deliberately set. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Chief James Montgomery said investigators have begun a criminal 
investigation of the fire at Pacific Awnings Corp., 4020 W. Carriage Drive, 
which was destroyed Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
"I can't release any of the details of the investigation because it might 
jeopardize our investigation," Montgomery said. 
</P>
<P>
The blaze caused $800,000 in damage to the structure and another $250,000 in 
damage to the building's contents, officials said. 
</P>
