<HEADLINE>
<P>
AREA ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CYPRESS PLAYS HOST TO SOFTBALL TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The girls' 16-and-under fast pitch state softball championships begin at noon 
today at Cypress Arnold Park. 
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one of Southern California's top travel teams will compete for the 
chance to represent Southern California at the national tournament Aug. 10-14 
in Midland, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
The junior Batbusters of Westminster, the defending national champion, and the 
runner-up Panthers of Cypress already have qualified for the national 
tournament. They are not entered in the double-elimination tournament, but 
defending state tournament champion Hot Stuff will compete, as will Rod Carew's 
Quicksilver team. 
</P>
<P>
Admission is free. Games begin today and continue Saturday and Sunday at 9 a.m. 
with the championship game at 1 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
