<HEADLINE>
<P>
PANEL PLANS FUND-RAISER FOR THEATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Backers of a 1,500-seat performing arts center in Mission Viejo are moving 
forward with plans for a fund-raising event and a broadening of focus to the 
entire south county area. 
</P>
<P>
More than 20 members of an advisory board for the theater met for the first 
time Wednesday, laying the groundwork for the fund-raiser Oct. 14 at the 
Mission Viejo Mall, according to board chairman Christian W. Keena, who also 
serves as mayor pro tem of Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
Keena said the group hopes to raise $100,000 at the event for a feasibility 
study and preliminary drawings for the theater, which the board would like to 
see located on the campus of Saddleback College. 
</P>
<P>
With representatives on the advisory board from the college, the Mission Viejo 
and Rancho Santa Margarita companies and the cities of San Juan Capistrano, 
Dana Point and San Clemente, Keena said, the project is becoming regional, 
rather than municipal. "The college," he said, "has become the focal point for 
the performing arts in south county." 
</P>
<P>
The DeBartolo Corp., which owns the shopping center, and the Mission Viejo Co. 
have contributed cash and staff support for the fund-raiser, which will 
celebrate the mall's 10th anniversary, Keena said. Tickets for the event, which 
includes food and entertainment, begin at $25. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ARTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; FUND RAISING; ARTS -- FINANCES; MISSION VIEJO (CA) -- 
CULTURE; SADDLEBACK COLLEGE 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
