<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
IRANIAN KURD LEADER, 2 OTHERS KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VIENNA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gunmen assassinated Iranian Kurdish opposition leader Abdolrahman Qassemlu and 
two other exiled Kurdish activists and wounded a man with an Iranian diplomatic 
passport as they met in Vienna, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
"The murders were politically motivated," Police Chief Werner Liebhart told a 
news conference. "We don't know what the meeting was about." 
</P>
<P>
Liebhart said the three killers, who fled, burst into an apartment in central 
Vienna where the four men had held talks Thursday evening and immediately 
opened fire. 
</P>
<P>
Qassemlu, 59, was secretary general of the pro-Iraqi Democratic Party of 
Kurdistan. In Tehran, independent sources who declined to be named said 
Qassemlu, who has led the Iranian Kurds against Tehran for over 20 years, had 
been negotiating a settlement with the leadership emerging in Tehran after the 
death of the Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
