DEATHS; 
</P>
<P>
IRWIN COMP OF PACKERS FAME DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WOODRUFF, Wis. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Irvin H. Comp, a member of the Green Bay Packers Hall of Fame, has died at age 
70. A native of Milwaukee, he played quarterback and defensive back for the 
Packers from 1943 through 1949. Comp was inducted into the Packers Hall of Fame 
in 1986. He died Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Comp won 12 letters at St. Benedict's College in Atchison, Kan. The Packers 
made him their second-round draft choice. 
</P>
<P>
Comp was the quarterback on the 1944 team that beat the New York Giants 14-7 
for the team's sixth championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
