<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
3 DEFECTORS ARRIVE IN W. GERMANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAMBURG, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three East German soccer players who defected from their team in Sweden have 
arrived in West Germany, the Bild newspaper said today. 
</P>
<P>
The three reported to the West German consulate in Goteborg on Wednesday and 
were put on a ship that took them to the West German port of Kiel, the 
newspaper said. They arrived Thursday, and Bild printed a photograph of the 
three walking from the vessel. 
</P>
<P>
Bild identified them as Jens Koenig, 24; Andre Koehler, 24, and Thomas Weiss, 
21. The report said the three hope to continue their careers in West Germany. 
</P>
<P>
They defected hours before their East German first-division team, Wismut Aue, 
played Orgryte IF of Sweden in a Toto Cup match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
