<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ferruzzi Fights Liquidation Order: Citing possible harm to the public, U.S. 
District Judge James Zagel denied a request for a temporary injunction by 
Ferruzzi Trading International SA and Ferruzzi USA Inc. to block a Chicago 
Board of Trade order that is forcing the firm to sell a huge quantity of 
soybean futures. The lawsuit sought the restraining order and a permanent 
injunction against the exchange's directive. Published reports have said the 
firm was the object of the directive because it was trying to corner the 
soybean market -- something Ferruzzi denies. 
</P>
